davide (davide@cad.gatech.edu) wrote:

:   basicaly, I guess I am asking, is there anyway to tell that the key
:   was limited to all ascii, (or some other limited pool) from the
:   output of the encryption program (I understand that this is probably


The most obvious sign is that a human is supplying the key!
That is why the user-supplied password or phrase is best
processed by a machine (say, MD5 or SHA) before being actually
used as a cryptographic key.

Entropy is context-sensitive.     :-)


